725107f-a.text:
(1)
20th Road (Old Bowery Bay Road), north side, east of 42nd Street, showing at the left, on the east side of a carriage path, the site of the Samuel H. Moore house of 1852. The Titus family occupied it from 1891-1896. The early history of this place is, that Samuel Moore purchased in 1684 a farm near the Poor Farm of Wm. Hallett Sr. Joseph Moore, his son, was the next owner followed by John Moore, a brother of Joseph. David, a son of John Moore, was next in line.
May, 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, showing a part of the Moore Farm at the left foreground.
May, 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3) and (4)
The same site, showing the gate posts which were removed in April 1925.
March 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
